1
00:00:01,290 --> 00:01:32,270
♪

2
00:01:35,030 --> 00:01:52,010
♪

3
00:01:52,010 --> 00:01:53,200
Good morning!

4
00:01:53,200 --> 00:01:56,040
(cranking)

5
00:01:56,040 --> 00:01:57,230
Ugh.

6
00:01:57,230 --> 00:02:00,240
As Confucius once said,
cleanliness is next

7
00:02:00,240 --> 00:02:02,210
to godliness.

8
00:02:02,210 --> 00:02:05,210
Or something like that.

9
00:02:05,210 --> 00:02:06,220
(breaking)

10
00:02:06,220 --> 00:02:09,140
Oh!

11
00:02:09,140 --> 00:02:11,230
(splash)

12
00:02:11,230 --> 00:02:14,270
♪

13
00:02:14,270 --> 00:02:16,050
(squawking)

14
00:02:16,050 --> 00:02:17,220
He slipped a disc in his back?

15
00:02:17,220 --> 00:02:20,020
Yep, Kori and Yoshi
decided to go to the clinic

16
00:02:20,020 --> 00:02:21,040
to help Dr. Gensai

17
00:02:21,040 --> 00:02:22,220
manage to get his work done.

18
00:02:22,220 --> 00:02:24,010
Wait a second,
was there a reason

19
00:02:24,010 --> 00:02:27,060
why you didn't volunteer
to go along, Kenshin?

20
00:02:27,060 --> 00:02:28,250
I mean, what do
those two really know

21
00:02:28,250 --> 00:02:31,100
about medicine, anyway?

22
00:02:31,100 --> 00:02:33,190
Who knows.

23
00:02:33,190 --> 00:02:35,060
They're actually
helping out Ms. Megumi

24
00:02:35,060 --> 00:02:38,090
'cause she will be
in charge today.

25
00:02:38,090 --> 00:02:41,040
Well, I wish him
a lot of luck, anyway.

26
00:02:41,040 --> 00:02:43,100
(crying)

27
00:02:43,100 --> 00:02:45,150
There's no need to cry,
there's a nice lady doctor

28
00:02:45,150 --> 00:02:47,200
here to help your earache, son.

29
00:02:47,200 --> 00:02:49,010
But I was here first!

30
00:02:49,010 --> 00:02:50,090
I know that, ma'am.

31
00:02:50,090 --> 00:02:53,100
Now that I've set the bone,
it's up to you to rest this leg,

32
00:02:53,100 --> 00:02:55,100
at least for a few weeks.

33
00:02:55,100 --> 00:02:56,070
Thank you.

34
00:02:56,070 --> 00:02:58,170
So, Kori, how's it going over there?

35
00:02:58,170 --> 00:02:59,210
(gasps)

36
00:02:59,210 --> 00:03:00,120
I've done it!

37
00:03:00,120 --> 00:03:01,100
Just take a look!

38
00:03:01,100 --> 00:03:02,180
I've come up with
a mystic cure

39
00:03:02,180 --> 00:03:04,110
for any severe head cold!

40
00:03:04,110 --> 00:03:06,100
I wonder what she'd do
for something serious.

41
00:03:06,100 --> 00:03:08,020
I think this patient
is all done.

42
00:03:08,020 --> 00:03:10,050
Who's the next lucky patient?

43
00:03:10,050 --> 00:03:11,290
Ms. Takin!

44
00:03:11,290 --> 00:03:14,110
♪

45
00:03:14,110 --> 00:03:17,060
Pretend earthquake!

46
00:03:17,060 --> 00:03:18,170
Children!

47
00:03:18,170 --> 00:03:21,050
(grimacing)

48
00:03:21,050 --> 00:03:23,050
This mixture I've made
should really help them.

49
00:03:23,050 --> 00:03:25,080
I would suggest drinking
this on an empty stomach,

50
00:03:25,080 --> 00:03:28,080
once early in the morning,
and once again at night.

51
00:03:28,080 --> 00:03:30,080
Thank you Ms. Megumi,
I will give you

52
00:03:30,080 --> 00:03:34,020
my only chicken as payment
for your services.

53
00:03:34,020 --> 00:03:36,230
That's much too generous,
I couldn't take your chicken.

54
00:03:36,230 --> 00:03:38,050
But, if you have
some eggs to spare

55
00:03:38,050 --> 00:03:39,080
that'd be great!

56
00:03:39,080 --> 00:03:41,110
And, I'll bring you
a little bok choy!

57
00:03:41,110 --> 00:03:43,010
Doctor, you,
it's an emergency,

58
00:03:43,010 --> 00:03:46,000
please help us!

59
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:47,020
What happened?

60
00:03:47,020 --> 00:03:49,040
Some guys from Himeji
we were gambling with

61
00:03:49,040 --> 00:03:50,190
started losing a lot
and they thought

62
00:03:50,190 --> 00:03:52,160
Ryu was cheating them at dice.

63
00:03:52,160 --> 00:03:53,210
So, they decided
to take it out on him

64
00:03:53,210 --> 00:03:54,260
with a couple of knives!

65
00:03:54,260 --> 00:03:55,250
Cut with the story,

66
00:03:55,250 --> 00:03:57,000
if you don't treat
this guy now, Megumi,

67
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:58,010
then he's gonna die!

68
00:03:58,010 --> 00:04:00,130
We'll do all that we can.

69
00:04:00,130 --> 00:04:02,130
Kori, start making
bandages right away!

70
00:04:02,130 --> 00:04:03,180
Right!

71
00:04:03,180 --> 00:04:05,180
Yoshi, get the antiseptic
and start cleaning his wounds.

72
00:04:05,180 --> 00:04:06,250
I'm gonna die!

73
00:04:06,250 --> 00:04:08,040
You just relax.

74
00:04:08,040 --> 00:04:11,240
Kori, I need you
to loosen his clothing.

75
00:04:11,240 --> 00:04:15,090
He's got three deep
stab wounds, Megumi!

76
00:04:15,090 --> 00:04:17,230
Then we've got to get started.

77
00:04:17,230 --> 00:04:21,210
But she's a woman, Sano,
how good a doctor can she be?

78
00:04:21,210 --> 00:04:23,210
This guy's in a lot worse shape
than I thought,

79
00:04:23,210 --> 00:04:25,170
we've got to stop his bleeding.

80
00:04:25,170 --> 00:04:26,150
All right,

81
00:04:26,150 --> 00:04:28,030
you three hold him still.

82
00:04:29,150 --> 00:04:35,030
♪

83
00:04:35,030 --> 00:04:36,070
This should help.

84
00:04:36,070 --> 00:04:38,220
The other lamp's running out.

85
00:04:38,220 --> 00:04:40,170
Thanks, Kori.

86
00:04:40,170 --> 00:05:00,030
♪

87
00:05:00,030 --> 00:05:02,100
Finally, we're finished.

88
00:05:02,100 --> 00:05:06,250
♪

89
00:05:06,250 --> 00:05:10,100
Now, all we can do is wait.

90
00:05:10,100 --> 00:05:25,290
♪

91
00:05:25,290 --> 00:05:28,120
She did a great job.

92
00:05:28,120 --> 00:05:33,040
♪

93
00:05:34,220 --> 00:05:37,060
(background chatter)

94
00:05:40,050 --> 00:05:42,050
Welcome to Lenny's!

95
00:05:42,050 --> 00:05:43,260
Hello! Table for one?

96
00:05:43,260 --> 00:05:45,270
For a woman doctor,
she sure did a stellar job

97
00:05:45,270 --> 00:05:47,230
of patching up Ryu!

98
00:05:47,230 --> 00:05:49,110
Without even flinching,
she sewed him up

99
00:05:49,110 --> 00:05:51,060
just like he was a kimono!

100
00:05:51,060 --> 00:05:53,290
And she's so beautiful,
I wouldn't mind her treating me!

101
00:05:53,290 --> 00:05:56,150
Help, I think I need a doctor!

102
00:05:56,150 --> 00:05:58,210
(munching)

103
00:05:58,210 --> 00:06:01,270
You two still owe
for your lunch last week.

104
00:06:01,270 --> 00:06:03,110
More rice, please.

105
00:06:03,110 --> 00:06:04,150
Oh?

106
00:06:04,150 --> 00:06:06,290
You must have a tapeworm, Sano.

107
00:06:06,290 --> 00:06:08,140
(laughing)

108
00:06:08,140 --> 00:06:09,180
So I'm hungry!

109
00:06:09,180 --> 00:06:13,280
♪

110
00:06:13,280 --> 00:06:16,280
(background chatter)

111
00:06:23,250 --> 00:06:25,280
Is the medicine going
to taste bitter, doctor?

112
00:06:25,280 --> 00:06:28,040
The bad news is
it doesn't taste good,

113
00:06:28,040 --> 00:06:31,110
but it will help
you breathe better.

114
00:06:31,110 --> 00:06:32,220
After she swallows
that, how long before

115
00:06:32,220 --> 00:06:34,050
we'll see an improvement?

116
00:06:34,050 --> 00:06:36,000
With a lung congestion
like Kaede has,

117
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:38,230
it might take two weeks
before we see any results.

118
00:06:38,230 --> 00:06:39,240
Be patient.

119
00:06:39,240 --> 00:06:41,210
To speed her recovery,
you could open the windows

120
00:06:41,210 --> 00:06:43,000
for some fresh air.

121
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:46,070
If it's a matter of more money,
I can pay whatever's necessary.

122
00:06:46,070 --> 00:06:47,260
I want her to have
the best remedy.

123
00:06:47,260 --> 00:06:49,230
Give us the most
expensive medicine!

124
00:06:49,230 --> 00:06:52,040
We want what's best
for our daughter.

125
00:06:52,040 --> 00:06:53,180
I'm giving her the same medicine

126
00:06:53,180 --> 00:06:55,260
Dr. Gensai prescribed
originally.

127
00:06:55,260 --> 00:07:00,230
It's not expensive,
but it does the job.

128
00:07:00,230 --> 00:07:03,050
They just don't
understand, Yoshi.

129
00:07:03,050 --> 00:07:05,080
They really think that
money can buy everything,

130
00:07:05,080 --> 00:07:07,010
including one's good health.

131
00:07:07,010 --> 00:07:09,110
You can't buy
a long life, either.

132
00:07:09,110 --> 00:07:12,010
You mean Kaede's not gonna live?

133
00:07:12,010 --> 00:07:13,220
Sure, she'll live,
as long as she takes

134
00:07:13,220 --> 00:07:15,100
her medicine like I told her to.

135
00:07:15,100 --> 00:07:16,290
She'll recover,
that along with

136
00:07:16,290 --> 00:07:19,290
plenty of bed rest will work.

137
00:07:19,290 --> 00:07:21,250
Believe it or not,
the bedrest is just

138
00:07:21,250 --> 00:07:24,280
as important as
taking her medicine.

139
00:07:24,280 --> 00:07:28,240
(footsteps)

140
00:07:28,240 --> 00:07:31,230
Ugh!

141
00:07:31,230 --> 00:07:32,190
What's the matter?

142
00:07:32,190 --> 00:07:33,280
It's my stomach!

143
00:07:33,280 --> 00:07:36,140
(wincing)

144
00:07:36,140 --> 00:07:39,260
It hurts!

145
00:07:39,260 --> 00:07:41,000
I need help!

146
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:43,170
Somebody run and get a doctor!

147
00:07:43,170 --> 00:07:45,000
Everybody relax,

148
00:07:45,000 --> 00:07:46,120
there's a doctor right here!

149
00:07:46,120 --> 00:07:48,000
We've got our own local doctor,

150
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:49,120
it's Megumi!

151
00:07:49,120 --> 00:07:51,200
You mean the lady doctor
from the clinic?

152
00:07:51,200 --> 00:07:53,220
I hear she does a good
job of healing people!

153
00:07:53,220 --> 00:07:55,000
If you're really a doctor,

154
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:57,260
please help!

155
00:07:57,260 --> 00:07:59,190
You're fine.

156
00:07:59,190 --> 00:08:01,120
There's nothing wrong with him.

157
00:08:01,120 --> 00:08:02,060
Huh?

158
00:08:02,060 --> 00:08:04,080
But I feel terrible!

159
00:08:04,080 --> 00:08:05,240
Where you goin', lady doctor?

160
00:08:05,240 --> 00:08:10,190
Can't you see that guy
needs your help?

161
00:08:10,190 --> 00:08:12,010
Didn't you take
some kind of oath

162
00:08:12,010 --> 00:08:13,280
to become a doctor?

163
00:08:13,280 --> 00:08:15,290
(crowd murmuring in agreement)

164
00:08:15,290 --> 00:08:18,240
The guy's obviously in pain,
and you're walking away?

165
00:08:18,240 --> 00:08:23,050
Yeah, you a doctor or a quack?

166
00:08:23,050 --> 00:08:25,020
So why is she
refusing to help him?

167
00:08:25,020 --> 00:08:26,030
I don't know.

168
00:08:26,030 --> 00:08:28,170
If it's a matter of money,
I'll pay for him!

169
00:08:28,170 --> 00:08:31,140
If he was really sick,
then I would help him.

170
00:08:31,140 --> 00:08:35,200
Now, excuse me.

171
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:37,270
Megumi, just where
are you going?

172
00:08:37,270 --> 00:08:40,190
Does someone need my help?

173
00:08:40,190 --> 00:08:42,090
I'm a shaman,
and I can cure

174
00:08:42,090 --> 00:08:43,270
almost any sickness!

175
00:08:43,270 --> 00:08:44,260
(clank)

176
00:08:44,260 --> 00:08:46,240
Yojimbo is my name.

177
00:08:46,240 --> 00:08:48,200
It has taken me many days
to come here from

178
00:08:48,200 --> 00:08:50,270
a mystical mountain far away.

179
00:08:50,270 --> 00:08:52,090
There, I was trained in medicine

180
00:08:52,090 --> 00:08:53,270
by artisan fairies.

181
00:08:53,270 --> 00:08:56,010
I am a conjurer,
and my healing spells

182
00:08:56,010 --> 00:08:58,100
work wonders always!

183
00:08:58,100 --> 00:08:59,250
This guy sounds great!

184
00:08:59,250 --> 00:09:01,290
Help, please cure me!

185
00:09:01,290 --> 00:09:03,150
I will.

186
00:09:03,150 --> 00:09:07,000
Hee-yah!

187
00:09:08,180 --> 00:09:10,200
Let there be light!

188
00:09:10,200 --> 00:09:13,070
Ee-ka-ka!

189
00:09:13,070 --> 00:09:17,110
(chanting gibberish)

190
00:09:17,110 --> 00:09:18,250
Ugh!

191
00:09:18,250 --> 00:09:22,160
And now...

192
00:09:22,160 --> 00:09:26,150
(chanting gibberish)

193
00:09:26,150 --> 00:09:34,100
♪

194
00:09:34,100 --> 00:09:35,230
Oh!

195
00:09:35,230 --> 00:09:40,290
♪

196
00:09:40,290 --> 00:09:45,280
Huh?

197
00:09:45,280 --> 00:09:48,070
Ah-ha!

198
00:09:48,070 --> 00:09:50,260
Yee!

199
00:09:50,260 --> 00:09:52,180
Now you must drink this.

200
00:09:52,180 --> 00:09:54,020
It contains enough healing power

201
00:09:54,020 --> 00:09:55,280
to move mountains!

202
00:09:55,280 --> 00:10:01,010
(gulping)

203
00:10:01,010 --> 00:10:02,290
Hey! I can't believe it!

204
00:10:02,290 --> 00:10:04,220
The pain's gone completely!

205
00:10:04,220 --> 00:10:06,000
Oh!

206
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:07,060
It's a real miracle!

207
00:10:07,060 --> 00:10:08,040
Wow, did you see that?

208
00:10:08,040 --> 00:10:09,120
He didn't even touch him!

209
00:10:09,120 --> 00:10:10,130
He's some kind

210
00:10:10,130 --> 00:10:12,120
of a miracle faith healer
that can cure almost

211
00:10:12,120 --> 00:10:13,270
any disease!

212
00:10:13,270 --> 00:10:14,290
Mr. Yojimbo,

213
00:10:14,290 --> 00:10:17,120
I have a sick aunt at home,
would you please help?

214
00:10:17,120 --> 00:10:19,200
My husband needs to be treated!

215
00:10:19,200 --> 00:10:23,080
Did you see that?

216
00:10:23,080 --> 00:10:26,000
Please help me!

217
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:27,250
Mmm, I see.

218
00:10:27,250 --> 00:10:29,030
Well, what do you think?

219
00:10:29,030 --> 00:10:30,270
Is it really possible
for someone to be cured

220
00:10:30,270 --> 00:10:31,200
of a sickness

221
00:10:31,200 --> 00:10:33,030
by a mountain witch doctor?

222
00:10:33,030 --> 00:10:34,050
Who knows.

223
00:10:34,050 --> 00:10:35,060
I saw it,
what he did

224
00:10:35,060 --> 00:10:36,170
was just amazing!

225
00:10:36,170 --> 00:10:39,110
And it sure made Megumi
look pretty inconsiderate.

226
00:10:39,110 --> 00:10:40,110
I couldn't believe it,

227
00:10:40,110 --> 00:10:42,190
she just left that
sick guy lying there.

228
00:10:42,190 --> 00:10:44,150
I think you're
misjudging Megumi,

229
00:10:44,150 --> 00:10:47,150
she must have seen something
that no one else there saw.

230
00:10:47,150 --> 00:10:48,190
What did she see?

231
00:10:48,190 --> 00:10:50,080
I have no idea,
I haven't talked

232
00:10:50,080 --> 00:10:51,210
to her about it.

233
00:10:51,210 --> 00:10:52,200
What?

234
00:10:55,090 --> 00:10:57,160
♪

235
00:10:57,160 --> 00:10:58,270
(crowd laughing)

236
00:10:58,270 --> 00:11:01,080
Our little show
really went very well.

237
00:11:01,080 --> 00:11:02,200
And our bigger plan
to discredit

238
00:11:02,200 --> 00:11:04,010
that lady doctor
is coming off

239
00:11:04,010 --> 00:11:05,000
without a hitch.

240
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:06,250
Soon, no one will go to her.

241
00:11:06,250 --> 00:11:09,090
And after word spreads
about your demonstration today,

242
00:11:09,090 --> 00:11:11,170
all of her patients
will be coming to us,

243
00:11:11,170 --> 00:11:13,210
right, Dr. Yojimbo?

244
00:11:13,210 --> 00:11:14,140
Ahh!

245
00:11:14,140 --> 00:11:15,210
You are correct!

246
00:11:15,210 --> 00:11:17,120
When the townspeople
hear how she left

247
00:11:17,120 --> 00:11:19,140
the man in pain
and how I handled things,

248
00:11:19,140 --> 00:11:22,270
we will rule this town!

249
00:11:22,270 --> 00:11:24,280
And since the people
think I can cure them,

250
00:11:24,280 --> 00:11:26,180
they will pay
whatever we ask!

251
00:11:26,180 --> 00:11:28,200
With as many sick people
as there are in that town,

252
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:29,150
we will be rich!

253
00:11:29,150 --> 00:11:30,160
All of us!

254
00:11:30,160 --> 00:11:31,150
Uh-huh.

255
00:11:31,150 --> 00:11:33,020
Nobody asked you,
now get us some more sake

256
00:11:33,020 --> 00:11:34,150
and don't waste any money on it,

257
00:11:34,150 --> 00:11:35,090
just steal it!

258
00:11:35,090 --> 00:11:37,170
Yes sir, right away.

259
00:11:37,170 --> 00:11:40,010
After we create suspicions
about the lady doctor,

260
00:11:40,010 --> 00:11:41,280
discrediting the other
doctors in town

261
00:11:41,280 --> 00:11:43,180
will be very easy.

262
00:11:46,110 --> 00:11:49,140
You don't think
we'll be cured here?

263
00:11:49,140 --> 00:11:50,260
Well, she cured me last time,

264
00:11:50,260 --> 00:11:52,080
but I've heard of
a new healer in town

265
00:11:52,080 --> 00:11:54,140
that's performing miracles.

266
00:11:54,140 --> 00:11:56,230
Well, maybe we should go
see that one, instead.

267
00:11:56,230 --> 00:11:58,200
Huh?

268
00:11:58,200 --> 00:12:03,090
♪

269
00:12:03,090 --> 00:12:05,090
Oh, if it isn't
that lady doctor.

270
00:12:05,090 --> 00:12:06,260
She is the one
who wouldn't help!

271
00:12:06,260 --> 00:12:09,080
I thought doctors had hearts!

272
00:12:09,080 --> 00:12:11,260
I'll put your mouth
where the sun doesn't shine!

273
00:12:11,260 --> 00:12:13,220
She's the one that's been
pretending to be a doctor,

274
00:12:13,220 --> 00:12:16,120
and she's not even trained!

275
00:12:16,120 --> 00:12:19,120
♪

276
00:12:19,120 --> 00:12:20,130
This is insane!

277
00:12:20,130 --> 00:12:22,180
Just what is going on here?

278
00:12:25,040 --> 00:12:27,210
(crowd chatter)

279
00:12:27,210 --> 00:12:30,020
-That dish is for table five.
-Mm-hmm.

280
00:12:30,020 --> 00:12:32,040
So what I've heard
is that this Yojimbo guy

281
00:12:32,040 --> 00:12:34,200
will see only patients
that have lots of money.

282
00:12:34,200 --> 00:12:37,010
All the people that go
to him have to pay 1,000 yen

283
00:12:37,010 --> 00:12:38,020
just to see him.

284
00:12:38,020 --> 00:12:39,230
And I understand he
charges a lot more for

285
00:12:39,230 --> 00:12:42,280
the special water
he chants over.

286
00:12:42,280 --> 00:12:44,100
All I know is,
the guys that

287
00:12:44,100 --> 00:12:45,270
are trying to discredit Megumi,

288
00:12:45,270 --> 00:12:48,190
all belong to
the Hishimanji group.

289
00:12:48,190 --> 00:12:50,040
Hishimanji?

290
00:12:50,040 --> 00:12:52,190
Yeah, that's the wild gang
that actually shot a cannon

291
00:12:52,190 --> 00:12:54,130
into the gambling hall in Edo.

292
00:12:54,130 --> 00:12:55,280
They're worse
than the Yakuza,

293
00:12:55,280 --> 00:12:57,030
because they'll do anything

294
00:12:57,030 --> 00:12:58,150
to take over.

295
00:12:58,150 --> 00:12:59,270
Sano, you're not eating.

296
00:12:59,270 --> 00:13:00,290
What is it?

297
00:13:00,290 --> 00:13:02,120
I've gotta go.

298
00:13:02,120 --> 00:13:04,270
A friend is in trouble,
and I've got a strong feeling

299
00:13:04,270 --> 00:13:09,100
that this person could
probably use my help.

300
00:13:09,100 --> 00:13:10,280
Well...

301
00:13:10,280 --> 00:13:13,080
♪

302
00:13:13,080 --> 00:13:15,010
What is it?

303
00:13:15,010 --> 00:13:16,130
Huh?

304
00:13:16,130 --> 00:13:18,180
(hooves clomping)

305
00:13:18,180 --> 00:13:22,130
♪

306
00:13:22,130 --> 00:13:24,100
She's ready to go!

307
00:13:24,100 --> 00:13:26,140
♪

308
00:13:26,140 --> 00:13:28,110
And just where are
you going with Kaede?

309
00:13:28,110 --> 00:13:29,160
She's too sick to be moved,

310
00:13:29,160 --> 00:13:31,220
she needs bedrest!

311
00:13:31,220 --> 00:13:34,100
You know, I think the whole town
thinks a big fake like you

312
00:13:34,100 --> 00:13:36,290
really needs a rest,
so why don't you bug off,

313
00:13:36,290 --> 00:13:38,120
got it?

314
00:13:38,120 --> 00:13:39,210
Hey now, wait!

315
00:13:39,210 --> 00:13:40,280
She can't be--

316
00:13:40,280 --> 00:13:42,210
I told you to get going!

317
00:13:42,210 --> 00:13:43,190
Ugh!

318
00:13:43,190 --> 00:13:46,200
Hey, that's enough!

319
00:13:46,200 --> 00:13:47,230
Ahh!

320
00:13:47,230 --> 00:13:48,260
(smack)

321
00:13:48,260 --> 00:13:50,070
Oof.

322
00:13:50,070 --> 00:13:51,140
You can't do this.

323
00:13:51,140 --> 00:13:52,240
You're wrong!

324
00:13:52,240 --> 00:13:54,250
(laughter)

325
00:13:54,250 --> 00:13:56,140
So you are the doctor
without a heart

326
00:13:56,140 --> 00:13:57,150
I've heard about.

327
00:13:57,150 --> 00:13:59,160
You cannot stop me
from healing this child,

328
00:13:59,160 --> 00:14:01,120
so take your sick ways with you!

329
00:14:01,120 --> 00:14:04,140
Now, you get away from here!

330
00:14:04,140 --> 00:14:07,240
No way, I won't!

331
00:14:07,240 --> 00:14:08,190
Yeah you--

332
00:14:08,190 --> 00:14:10,210
Oof!

333
00:14:10,210 --> 00:14:12,200
Why are you taking Kaede away?

334
00:14:12,200 --> 00:14:15,180
Don't you realize by doing this,
you're risking her life?

335
00:14:15,180 --> 00:14:16,220
Oh!

336
00:14:16,220 --> 00:14:18,230
Oof!

337
00:14:18,230 --> 00:14:20,040
Wait!

338
00:14:20,040 --> 00:14:22,060
I've just got to stop them!

339
00:14:22,060 --> 00:14:25,040
No!

340
00:14:25,040 --> 00:14:27,060
Don't worry!

341
00:14:27,060 --> 00:14:30,280
I'll find out where they go!

342
00:14:30,280 --> 00:14:33,120
(chanting gibberish)

343
00:14:33,120 --> 00:15:07,210
♪

344
00:15:07,210 --> 00:15:08,140
Yeah-ha!

345
00:15:08,140 --> 00:15:09,120
And now--

346
00:15:09,120 --> 00:15:11,160
You stop that right now!

347
00:15:11,160 --> 00:15:15,170
(panting)

348
00:15:15,170 --> 00:15:19,050
How dare you burst in
in the middle of my chant?

349
00:15:19,050 --> 00:15:21,110
Mr. Yoshinoya,
you don't understand.

350
00:15:21,110 --> 00:15:23,280
You can't buy Kaede's health,
she needs her medicine

351
00:15:23,280 --> 00:15:24,290
to get better.

352
00:15:24,290 --> 00:15:26,140
Please leave us alone.

353
00:15:26,140 --> 00:15:27,090
Hold it!

354
00:15:27,090 --> 00:15:28,170
Why should we listen to you?

355
00:15:28,170 --> 00:15:30,090
You saw that sick man,
and instead of helping

356
00:15:30,090 --> 00:15:31,140
you just walked away!

357
00:15:31,140 --> 00:15:34,080
That man I walked away from
was just pretending to be sick.

358
00:15:34,080 --> 00:15:36,260
Yojimbo and his cronies
are fooling everyone.

359
00:15:36,260 --> 00:15:39,010
(grunting)

360
00:15:39,010 --> 00:15:41,000
She's just lying to you!

361
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:42,010
You!

362
00:15:42,010 --> 00:15:43,050
Ugh!

363
00:15:43,050 --> 00:15:45,110
Just keep your mouth shut, kid,
and you won't get hurt.

364
00:15:45,110 --> 00:15:46,030
Folks!

365
00:15:46,030 --> 00:15:49,140
You're the guy!
The guy that pretended to be sick!

366
00:15:49,140 --> 00:15:52,150
You know what the Hishimanji
do to guys with a loose tongue?

367
00:15:52,150 --> 00:15:53,200
We cut it off!

368
00:15:53,200 --> 00:15:54,200
(laughs)

369
00:15:54,200 --> 00:15:56,100
Then this is a scam!

370
00:15:56,100 --> 00:15:58,040
Get over there
with the rest of 'em!

371
00:15:58,040 --> 00:15:59,020
Wait!

372
00:15:59,020 --> 00:16:01,170
You can't just keep
us all here forever!

373
00:16:01,170 --> 00:16:03,220
(laughs)

374
00:16:03,220 --> 00:16:06,020
Oh yeah?

375
00:16:06,020 --> 00:16:07,120
(smack)

376
00:16:07,120 --> 00:16:11,010
(gasps)

377
00:16:11,010 --> 00:16:14,170
I've been looking
for you, Hishimaji.

378
00:16:14,170 --> 00:16:16,110
You were picking on my friend.

379
00:16:16,110 --> 00:16:17,200
It's time for you
to get picked on.

380
00:16:17,200 --> 00:16:18,130
All right!

381
00:16:18,130 --> 00:16:20,210
You got it, boy!

382
00:16:20,210 --> 00:16:24,000
So let's do it!

383
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:26,170
Ahh!

384
00:16:26,170 --> 00:16:31,250
♪

385
00:16:31,250 --> 00:16:35,280
Ugh!

386
00:16:35,280 --> 00:16:37,110
(thud)

387
00:16:37,110 --> 00:16:40,070
♪

388
00:16:40,070 --> 00:16:41,150
(smack)

389
00:16:41,150 --> 00:16:43,010
Ahh!

390
00:16:43,010 --> 00:16:46,080
Run and get Kaede!

391
00:16:46,080 --> 00:16:49,110
(smack)

392
00:16:49,110 --> 00:16:51,050
Kaede!

393
00:16:51,050 --> 00:16:52,250
Don't even try it,
you big fake!

394
00:16:52,250 --> 00:16:55,220
You're a big loser!

395
00:16:55,220 --> 00:16:57,090
(laughs)

396
00:16:57,090 --> 00:17:00,100
(smack)

397
00:17:00,100 --> 00:17:01,230
(whack)

398
00:17:01,230 --> 00:17:04,060
Whoa!

399
00:17:04,060 --> 00:17:06,210
(yelling)

400
00:17:06,210 --> 00:17:09,010
(thud)

401
00:17:09,010 --> 00:17:10,250
Oof!

402
00:17:10,250 --> 00:17:13,110
Doctor, please help me.

403
00:17:13,110 --> 00:17:15,280
This should help, Kaede.

404
00:17:15,280 --> 00:17:17,240
I want to thank you very much.

405
00:17:17,240 --> 00:17:20,180
Please accept our
sincerest apology.

406
00:17:20,180 --> 00:17:22,180
I accept your apology,
but it's important

407
00:17:22,180 --> 00:17:24,000
that you both
understand something

408
00:17:24,000 --> 00:17:26,160
about the healing process.

409
00:17:26,160 --> 00:17:27,130
To cure a sickness,

410
00:17:27,130 --> 00:17:29,030
there are several
factors involved.

411
00:17:29,030 --> 00:17:30,290
The patient must follow
the doctor's advice,

412
00:17:30,290 --> 00:17:33,000
take their medicine,
and in the case of Kaede,

413
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:34,220
she also needs your help.

414
00:17:34,220 --> 00:17:37,200
You both must give her
your love and support.

415
00:17:37,200 --> 00:17:38,170
Oh no it's a--

416
00:17:38,170 --> 00:17:39,190
Get down!

417
00:17:39,190 --> 00:17:43,170
(explosion)

418
00:17:43,170 --> 00:17:45,250
(laughs)

419
00:17:45,250 --> 00:17:47,090
So you think you're
courageous enough

420
00:17:47,090 --> 00:17:49,200
to try to take on
the Hishimanji?

421
00:17:49,200 --> 00:17:51,200
Huh?

422
00:17:51,200 --> 00:17:54,170
(laughs)

423
00:17:54,170 --> 00:17:57,170
One more time!

424
00:17:57,170 --> 00:17:59,100
Looks like they brought
in heavy artillery!

425
00:17:59,100 --> 00:18:00,250
They're probably
gonna blow us apart!

426
00:18:00,250 --> 00:18:02,160
Fire!

427
00:18:02,160 --> 00:18:04,250
(boom)

428
00:18:04,250 --> 00:18:07,010
(crash)

429
00:18:07,010 --> 00:18:09,220
Hey, I'm still inside!

430
00:18:09,220 --> 00:18:11,280
You're wrecking my house!

431
00:18:11,280 --> 00:18:13,180
Ugh!

432
00:18:13,180 --> 00:18:15,100
(laughs)

433
00:18:15,100 --> 00:18:17,010
If you want to live,
you'd better get out

434
00:18:17,010 --> 00:18:19,080
of that house right now!

435
00:18:19,080 --> 00:18:22,030
You certainly have a way
of treating your friends.

436
00:18:22,030 --> 00:18:23,180
Some say sickness
can be the result

437
00:18:23,180 --> 00:18:25,110
of a sick mind,
so I've come to see

438
00:18:25,110 --> 00:18:27,250
that my friends are all right,
and to see if you're capable

439
00:18:27,250 --> 00:18:29,090
of being cured.

440
00:18:29,090 --> 00:18:30,110
Kenshin!

441
00:18:30,110 --> 00:18:31,190
So, are you and
your gang willing

442
00:18:31,190 --> 00:18:33,130
to leave town peacefully?

443
00:18:33,130 --> 00:18:34,150
Well, I'd like to answer

444
00:18:34,150 --> 00:18:36,280
your question in a way
you're sure to understand,

445
00:18:36,280 --> 00:18:39,210
so here's my explosive answer!

446
00:18:39,210 --> 00:18:40,250
Hah!

447
00:18:40,250 --> 00:18:42,170
Fire!

448
00:18:42,170 --> 00:18:45,200
(zoom)

449
00:18:45,200 --> 00:18:48,070
Kenshin!

450
00:18:48,070 --> 00:18:51,000
(slice)

451
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:53,000
Yeah!

452
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:54,140
Best thing about
a reverse edge sword

453
00:18:54,140 --> 00:18:56,280
is it cuts everything
but people very well.

454
00:18:56,280 --> 00:18:57,160
Quiet!

455
00:18:57,160 --> 00:18:59,290
Go ahead, kill him!

456
00:18:59,290 --> 00:19:02,190
(crowd yelling)

457
00:19:02,190 --> 00:19:08,040
♪

458
00:19:08,040 --> 00:19:09,290
(zoom)

459
00:19:09,290 --> 00:19:14,120
♪

460
00:19:14,120 --> 00:19:16,010
Ugh!

461
00:19:16,010 --> 00:19:18,040
Ahh!

462
00:19:18,040 --> 00:19:22,050
You Hishimanji
can't match Kenshin!

463
00:19:22,050 --> 00:19:23,110
(clink)

464
00:19:23,110 --> 00:19:25,240
Whaa-ha-hah!

465
00:19:25,240 --> 00:19:27,210
I feel so stressed,
I need help,

466
00:19:27,210 --> 00:19:29,280
I feel like my
colon's gonna burst!

467
00:19:29,280 --> 00:19:31,020
Whah!

468
00:19:31,020 --> 00:19:32,250
Well then, it's time
to let the chanting begin,

469
00:19:32,250 --> 00:19:34,070
Shaman Breath!

470
00:19:34,070 --> 00:19:37,070
But that won't do me any good,
that stuff was just fake!

471
00:19:37,070 --> 00:19:38,190
A-ha, finally the truth!

472
00:19:38,190 --> 00:19:39,110
You're no healer!

473
00:19:39,110 --> 00:19:40,120
You're a fake!

474
00:19:40,120 --> 00:19:41,190
He's right!

475
00:19:41,190 --> 00:19:42,200
Well, I could help.

476
00:19:42,200 --> 00:19:45,010
After all, stress-related
colon trouble can lead

477
00:19:45,010 --> 00:19:46,170
to insanity!

478
00:19:46,170 --> 00:19:48,230
But, if you confess
to the townspeople,

479
00:19:48,230 --> 00:19:51,120
I'll help.

480
00:19:51,120 --> 00:19:52,270
Uh, what happened here?

481
00:19:52,270 --> 00:19:56,230
Dr. Yojimbo's house
has been destroyed!

482
00:19:56,230 --> 00:19:58,090
It's nothing, really,
he just wanted

483
00:19:58,090 --> 00:19:59,160
a little remodeling.

484
00:19:59,160 --> 00:20:01,230
Hey, look everyone,
I got a confession here

485
00:20:01,230 --> 00:20:05,180
signed by Yojimbo,
saying he's a fake doctor!

486
00:20:05,180 --> 00:20:07,280
You better come by
the clinic later.

487
00:20:07,280 --> 00:20:08,260
(gasping)

488
00:20:08,260 --> 00:20:10,210
Why don't you let
those lowlifes alone?

489
00:20:10,210 --> 00:20:11,230
Stop that talk.

490
00:20:11,230 --> 00:20:13,290
Being a doctor
requires me to treat--

491
00:20:13,290 --> 00:20:14,270
Oh!

492
00:20:14,270 --> 00:20:16,030
Sano, are you jealous?

493
00:20:16,030 --> 00:20:17,140
Nah, it's just that
if you treat everyone

494
00:20:17,140 --> 00:20:18,290
that tangles with me,
you won't have time

495
00:20:18,290 --> 00:20:21,230
for those that really need it.

496
00:20:21,230 --> 00:20:29,050
♪

497
00:20:29,050 --> 00:20:30,260
Yojimbo fully recovered
from his ailment

498
00:20:30,260 --> 00:20:32,210
after you treated him.

499
00:20:32,210 --> 00:20:33,290
So, what kind of medicine
did you give him

500
00:20:33,290 --> 00:20:37,010
to take, anyway?

501
00:20:37,010 --> 00:20:39,160
(giggling)

502
00:20:39,160 --> 00:20:41,060
I probably shouldn't admit this,

503
00:20:41,060 --> 00:20:42,200
and don't tell anyone,

504
00:20:42,200 --> 00:20:46,130
but I gave him just plain water!

505
00:20:46,130 --> 00:20:50,150
Can you say placebo?

506
00:20:50,150 --> 00:20:51,260
So now that your back's better,

507
00:20:51,260 --> 00:20:53,090
how does it feel
to be working again,

508
00:20:53,090 --> 00:20:54,240
Dr. Gensai?

509
00:20:54,240 --> 00:20:56,150
Well, it's nice
to be busy again,

510
00:20:56,150 --> 00:20:57,210
but everyone asks,

511
00:20:57,210 --> 00:21:00,290
"Where's the lady doctor,"
when I come out!

512
00:21:00,290 --> 00:21:02,270
They really say that?

513
00:21:02,270 --> 00:21:04,060
I wish people were as interested

514
00:21:04,060 --> 00:21:06,050
in joining a dojo,
as Megumi's patients

515
00:21:06,050 --> 00:21:07,160
are interested in her.

516
00:21:07,160 --> 00:21:09,110
If you were as smart
and pretty as Megumi,

517
00:21:09,110 --> 00:21:11,200
more people would be
interested in you!

518
00:21:11,200 --> 00:21:12,270
What did you say!

519
00:21:12,270 --> 00:21:15,100
-Oh boy.
-Yoshi, ugh!

520
00:21:15,100 --> 00:21:16,020
Those two.

521
00:21:16,020 --> 00:21:18,110
They're like oil and water!

522
00:21:18,110 --> 00:21:21,020
I think this lady doctor's
the best in town!

523
00:21:21,020 --> 00:21:22,270
But there is something
that as a good a doctor

524
00:21:22,270 --> 00:21:24,230
as she is,
even she can't cure.

525
00:21:24,230 --> 00:21:26,060
And Sano's got it!

526
00:21:26,060 --> 00:21:27,190
Next, please!

527
00:21:27,190 --> 00:21:32,160
I can cure anyone that's sick
unless they're lovesick.

528
00:21:32,160 --> 00:21:35,200
♪

529
00:21:37,120 --> 00:23:12,050
♪

